<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>Before I post your updated list I would like to give you a little bit of information on the notes I have made below each item.<namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT> – This means that a few of the development team members are looking into ways to implement the item.&nbsp; This does not guarantee that the item will be implemented; however we may see changes made in the future.&nbsp; The Community Team plans to give updates on these types of items every 2 weeks, even if it’s just a “no change since the last update”</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed </FONT>– This is almost just like being evaluated however these items the development team is totally undecided if they want to implement or how to do so.&nbsp; The Community Team plans to give updates on these types of items every 2 weeks, even if it’s just a “no change since the last update”</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Done</FONT> – This means that the development team has implemented this item and it’s currently on live servers.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently on Test server</FONT> – This means that the development team has implement this item and it’s currently on test server, watch for future updates for implementation on the live servers.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana?><FONT color=#ff0000>This one I need your help on </FONT>– This means we don’t have enough information to make any type of decision on how to implement.&nbsp; Threads will be started by me to get your feedback.</SPAN><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>No changes planned at this time</FONT> – This means that the development team has decided at this time not to implement this item.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>Items that are marked done will be removed from the top 10 issues lists and you as a class will be able to replace those with new issues.&nbsp; Watch for posts on this in the next week, your class correspondents will be helping SOE update your top 10 issues lists with these new items.&nbsp; If your top issues list was less then 10 issues to begin with you will be able to add more issues.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>You as a class will have the option to replace items that are marked as “no changes planned at this time” with new items or leave them on the list.&nbsp; Please understand that leaving them on the list does not mean that they will eventually be implemented however it does mean that the class as a whole still feels that these are valid issues and would like implementation eventually.&nbsp; One thing to note, we will not be responding to requests as to why something is classified the way it is.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>This post will be locked and updated bi-weekly.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>--</SPAN></P><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>
<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; Arial?>Monk - </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>1) Monk mitigation. Parses reveal that monk mitigation is not only poor, but laughably poor. This thread here: <A href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=45252.topic" target=_blank><SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: windowtext?><FONT color=#ffff00>http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=45252.topic</FONT></SPAN></A></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>That thread reveals a pretty low "soft" cap on monk AC. This is bad for the game from a designer standpoint. Why? Because new armor is simply not needed for any other statistic besides hit points.&nbsp; It makes itemization a serious issue for monks. Armor class is basically meaningless for the class.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>2) Monk relative DPS. Warriors, Rangers, Berserkers all parse very very close to monks in DPS. Whereas Rogues parse out well ahead of the rest of the pack. The relative gap is distorted. Here's a nice little reference thread: <A href="http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=3803" target=_blank><SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: windowtext?><FONT color=#ffff00>http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=3803</FONT></SPAN></A></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>This needs some consideration, due to the fact that monks have only two roles. That of pulling, and that of DPS. If the DPS is relatively as lackluster as it measures out to be, then the class needs to be given some sort of power in other areas to compensate. Or the DPS gap between monks and their competitors needs to be widened a smidge.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>5a- Special Attack DPS. Frenzy is pretty darn close to Flying Kick in terms of DPS. And yet Flying Kick has never been close to backstab in terms of DPS. Why is it rogue special attack DPS can maintain such a solid, concrete advantage, but the monk special attack DPS can easily be ignored when creating new classes like that?</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>5b- Monk naked fist damage. At this point in the game, you'd do well to put monk fist damage back to what it was on Planes of Power release ... 18 damage, 20 delay at level 65. 15/20 is a joke.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>5c- Monk role as best DPS from "any angle" ... it's been suggested that the class could be given some sort of riposte immunity to allow them to attack raid level monsters from the frontal arc with little to zero penalty. For a raiding monk this would be a nice little boost to relative DPS (positioning would no longer be hampering DPS as a monk could get into&nbsp;a less crowded area of the monster, as well as help even out push) and could eventually give monks a more refined or specialized raid role (that of positioning). I mention this here, because Kavhok and Rytan have mentioned it on Monkly Biz ... because it concerns monk relative DPS specifically ... and because Return Kick being as broken as it is, would mean that the ability, if put live to test, would turn out to be affected by the broken-ness of Return Kick and Double Riposte. So keep that in mind. I also bring it up because the description of Monks being the best DPS from "any angle" is a broken description. That's not the way everquest functions. DPS crowds the backs of monsters, due to monster defenses being lower from back there, and due to ripostes and other nasty things like Area Effects not affecting the back arc in many situations. The risks for standing anywhere but behind a monster is simply too high, so monks being the best DPS from angles besides the back, is simply a joke in terms of actual game play.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>3) Monk Itemization.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>4a- The Weight of Gates of Discord Monk armors is extremely high. That needs to be fixed. Even the monk class only armor is too heavy. The monk class still does have an AC penalty for going overweight. And Packrat supposedly doesn't affect that portion of weight. <FONT color=#ff0000>(<SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: red?>Done)</SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>4b- The Monk mitigation nerf was done, according to the patches (see one of my other posts for the long winded details of those patches) mostly due to the large amount of "All/All items" that proliferated EverQuest during Velious and Luclin. Well that itemization issue, to justify the nerf, needs to continue. Which means Monks need to have 125 AC BPs and 100 AC pants. Or else the monk mitigation nerf is simply stacking a penalty onto an itemization issue that doesn't exist. <FONT color=#ff0000>(<SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: red?>Currently being discussed)</SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>4c- Monk DPS through weapons is extremely poor in the areas of the very mudflated levels of 55 to non-raiding 65.&nbsp; The market is basically filled with things like War Marshall's Bladed Staff, Copper Hammer of Striking, Windblade, etc., etc., etc. Whereas monks are still scraping to nab Golden Wraps of the Compact/Waning Light Katar, or Staff of Flowing Water. For a class that is supposed to be DPS oriented, the gap at that "level" of the game is pretty small between them and the rest of the world. Rogues, at least, still have backstab to keep them ahead. <FONT color=#ff0000>(<SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: red?>Currently being evaluated)</SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>4) Feign Death failure rate. It's a long-standing joke among the class. At 200 skill level, one should not fall to the ground as often as one does.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>The development team is considering lowering the feign death failure rate.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>5) Return Kick - AA. This AA has been broken since Luclin was launched. It and Double Riposte are pretty meaningless to begin with, due to the fact that only the main tank stands in front of most monsters these days, but even so, Return Kick could use some looking at.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>6) Leather armor graphics. Since monks became tied to the beastlord and druid classes in the great "clumping" of armor types, all the armor has ended up being the leather graphic (as there is no robe models for halflings or trolls and ogres ... and the monk specific armor set is obviously only on humans and iksars). There are no more robes. There's no more gi's. There's no more fist "wraps" or wrist "wraps" ... there's no more pants that look pants, just the little leather knickers. The class already has a hard enough time carving out its own niche and identity, but the graphic presentation of the class is so horrendously common, that we simply blend in, looking like a human druid most of the time. This is a far cry from the days of monks with slick tatooed chests or long flowing robes of the lost circle. Sleeper's Tomb should not be the last place a monk could ever loot a "robe."</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Done</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>7) Planeswalk. Its duration is so short and its endurance cost is so high and its refresh timer is so long, that its effect is simply not worth ever clicking. Make this movement speed increase stack with all other movement speed buffs, and it'd be worth the cost in endurance and refresh. And its short duration would make sense. Make it work like Speed Focus or Hundred Fists in that it will stack with anything and everything. Let it actually be a monk's "run for your life!" discipline. Because in its current form, it's broken.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Done</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>8) Monk epic. It has no Endurance on it. The Berserker Epic does. That needs to fixed. In fact, all MELEE only epics need endurance added. Endurance is, after all, a melee centric concept.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>9) Purify Body refresh timer. Purify Soul had its refresh timer reduced many many patches ago. Purify Body has not had its refresh timer touched. The cleric and monk version cost the same amount of AA and the same amount of AA to upgrade through the PoP upgrade. The refresh timers should be equal.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>10) Animations. 2hb animation is really really bad. As is the whole Tail Rake fiasco (one of the truly uniquely Iksar aspects of Everquest was pretty much ruined by Luclin animations and the Dragon Punch AA).</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>Animation changes for current models is not something we considering.<SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>However new character models are in the near future which will fix this problem.</FONT><FONT face="Century Gothic"><FONT size=2></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P></DIV></SPAN></DIV>
<P>Message Edited by Brenlo on <SPAN class=date_text>07-12-2004</SPAN> <SPAN class=time_text>10:04 AM</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN class=time_text><FONT color=#ff00ff>Changed #1 <SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>Monk mitigation from "<SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>No changes planned at this time" to "<SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>Currently being evaluated"</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P>Message Edited by Ashlanne on <SPAN class=date_text>07-15-2004</SPAN> <SPAN class=time_text>10:23 AM</SPAN></P><p>Message Edited by Ashlanne on <span class=date_text>07-16-2004</span> <span class=time_text>10:01 AM</span>
