<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Monk - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;05/06/05</FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??></SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>&nbsp; Monk mitigation -</B> </SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>This is being considered as part of round #1 of the class Re-Envision process.&nbsp; Some changes are currently on the Live Server.</STRONG>&nbsp; <EM>Notes from Kavhok - This first change was very simple - we put monks back at the same AC cap they used to have and gave them an over-the-cap return equal to rangers.&nbsp; We are currently evaluating the changes and are willing to make more if we think monks need it.</EM></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;></SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>2)<B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monk relative DPS -</B> </SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS evaluation for all classes has begun and will be the focus of part #2 of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><FONT size=2><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Monk Itemization -</B></SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;> <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated<FONT size=2></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>4)&nbsp;<STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Innate increase in runspeed - <FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red; **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><BR></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>There have been several threads on this.&nbsp; It is felt that an increase in runspeed on all levels will improve our pulling capabilities.&nbsp; The numbers that have been thrown around are 10-20% increase.</P></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;></SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??><STRONG>Reduce mend timer AA - <FONT color=#ff0000>NEW</FONT></STRONG></SPAN></B></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Leather armor graphics</B> </SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Discipline stacking and timer issues.</B>&nbsp; A lot of monks feel throw stone should not be on the same timer as phantom lull and planes walk should not be with healing will.&nbsp; Whirlwind also has a very long reuse timer and its tied to stonestance and earth walk, which are some life saving disciplines while pulling.&nbsp; </SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated.</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></P><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;>
<DIV><EM><STRONG>Suggested Changed - </STRONG></EM></DIV>
<DIV>A solution to the timer issues is to keep them linked however, say when a monk uses whirlwind instead of waiting 40 min for stonestance to come back, it comes back in 4 min as if it was on its regular timer.&nbsp; This will let us use our more power disciplins more often but will still keep it so we cannot chain use the disciplins.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So if&nbsp;whirlwind is used, both it and stone would grey out but stone would refresh as normal.&nbsp; If stone was used&nbsp;they would both grey out but since the quicker timer was the one used both would refresh as they do now.</DIV></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??><STRONG>8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Add more benifits for staying under weight <SPAN Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red; **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; Verdana? **SMURF**?COLOR:><SPAN>Currently being evaluated</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0.5in? 0pt></FONT></SPAN><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??><STRONG>Suggested benifits - </STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>Innate increase to runspeed</SPAN></DIV>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>Avoidance </SPAN></DIV>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>Attack speed. </SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>9)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <STRONG>Innate increase in avoidance</STRONG> - <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG><SPAN Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red; **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; Verdana? **SMURF**?COLOR:><SPAN><STRONG>Currently being evaluated</STRONG></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman??>10) &nbsp;<B>Ranged item stats.</B>&nbsp; Monks have to lose stats while pulling due to losing their range item.&nbsp; Some suggestions have been made of using only the ammo slot to throw from.&nbsp; Putting more monk throw able items in game with good stats with a drop rate which makes them a viable pulling tool instead of a rare stat item.&nbsp; More trade skill items with stats so they can be made and sold.&nbsp; </SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG><SPAN red; **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><BR></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></FONT><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></FONT><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><SPAN New ?Times FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: 12pt; Roman?? red;><STRONG><EM>Propose Solution</EM></STRONG>: To <SPAN>insure that the ammo slot is used as the primary sorce of expendeture of thrown items.&nbsp; With this, place throwing weapons in the game with appropriate stats to be used in the range slot.&nbsp; The ammo should not have to be the same as the thrown weapon and the highest range should be used for distance.&nbsp; These items used for stats should be no-drop and level required to prevent tweeking.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P></DIV></DIV><p>Message Edited by Ashlanne on <span class=date_text>05-12-2005</span> <span class=time_text>12:25 PM</span>
