			<DIV><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??><FONT color=#ff00ff><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; Arial?><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??><FONT color=#ff00ff><STRONG>Monk - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;06/03/05</STRONG></FONT></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??></SPAN></FONT><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??><STRONG>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monk mitigation -</STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff><FONT color=#ff00ff><STRONG> </STRONG></SPAN><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Done, are we ready to remove this from the list?</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:></FONT><FONT color=#ff00ff></P></FONT><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>2)<B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monk relative DPS -</B> </SPAN><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS evaluation for all classes has begun and will be the focus of part #2 of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><FONT size=2><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></FONT></FONT></SPAN> 
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Monk Itemization -</B></SPAN><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;> <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated<FONT size=2></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>4)&nbsp;<STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Innate increase in runspeed - <FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red; **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><BR></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>There have been several threads on this.&nbsp; It is felt that an increase in runspeed on all levels will improve our pulling capabilities.&nbsp; The numbers that have been thrown around are 10-20% increase.</P></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??><STRONG>5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reduce mend timer AA - <FONT color=#ff0000>NEW, new details have been submitted</FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>
<DIV><EM><STRONG>Suggested Changed - </STRONG></EM></DIV>
<DIV>Hastened Mend: 5 levels cost: 5,5,5,5,5 6% reduction per level.<BR>Mend = 6min refresh = 360 seconds. 6% = 21.6 seconds, 5 x 21.6 = 108 second, total refresh 4:12secs. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It has been discussed that it would be a good idea to split among the levels instead of having to get to level 70 to be able to start working on these.&nbsp; There has been some discussion over cost but no alternatives have been given so as of right now this is what is being proposes.</DIV></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Leather armor graphics</B> </SPAN><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??>7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Discipline stacking and timer issues.</B>&nbsp; A lot of monks feel throw stone should not be on the same timer as phantom lull and planes walk should not be with healing will.&nbsp; Whirlwind also has a very long reuse timer and its tied to stonestance and earth walk, which are some life saving disciplines while pulling.&nbsp; </SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated.</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></P><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? red;><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman?? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red;>
<DIV><EM><STRONG>Suggested Changed - </STRONG></EM></DIV>
<DIV>A solution to the timer issues is to keep them linked however, say when a monk uses whirlwind instead of waiting 40 min for stonestance to come back, it comes back in 4 min as if it was on its regular timer.&nbsp; This will let us use our more power disciplins more often but will still keep it so we cannot chain use the disciplins.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So if&nbsp;whirlwind is used, both it and stone would grey out but stone would refresh as normal.&nbsp; If stone was used&nbsp;they would both grey out but since the quicker timer was the one used both would refresh as they do now.</DIV></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??><STRONG>8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Add more benifits for staying under weight <SPAN Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red; **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><SPAN #cccccc; Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:><SPAN>Currently being evaluated</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0.5in? 0pt></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: 12pt; ?Times New Roman??><STRONG><EM>Suggested benifits -</EM> </STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL>
<LI>
